Package dynamicalSystems

Class Summary
Condition This class represents the condition to a given IfThenElse object.
Converter A Converter is a auxiliary variable that holds some values that will be used by Flows and others Converters, along the time intervals
Element An Element is the principal part of a Dynamic System.
Entity A Entity is either an Element, or a Relationship, or an IfThenElse.
Flow A Flow is an Element that is interrelated with the Stocks, meaning that something is being subtracted/added from/to Stock.
IfThenElse An IfThenElse object is formed by a Condition,and Two possible solution.
LookUp A lookUp table is a table containing several lines.
Relationship This class manages how the system entities, are interrelated.
Row A Row is one line in the lookUp table For each input, there is an output.
Simulation This class manages all the model Here, happens the control about all elements contained in simulation
Stock A Stock uses the input or the output given by flows (inflows,outFlows), to add or to subtract its values.
